<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-74-0836 </DOCNO><TEXT>Opencast coalmining has been undertaken in Britain since 1942, but nationalpolicy towards its role in the energy market has fluctuated, and todaythere is a growing awareness of its detrimental impact on the environment.This paper explores the changing policy background since 1974 and, throughan examination of recent planning appeal decisions, assesses the weightplaced on the competing factors underlying the present formulation ofgovernment policy. It is submitted that at present government has failedto formulate a coherent policy in terms of land-use and that the costof this failure is a continued erosion of the environment. 28 refs.</TEXT></DOC>